@startuml


title Panel Forensic Engine - Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Workflow\n(Slash Command)" as Trigger
participant "Kana Agent\n(Persona)" as Agent
participant "Panel Forensic Skill\n(Contract)" as Skill
participant "manga-ocr\n(MCP Tool)" as OCRTool
participant "Execution Steps\n(Micro-files)" as Steps
database "State\n(forensic-state.json)" as State

== 1. Activation & Context Load ==
User -> Trigger: /panel-forensic [image_path]
Trigger -> Agent: Load 'panel-forensic-analyst' Persona
Agent -> Skill: Mount 'panel-forensic/SKILL.md'
Skill -> Skill: Inject 'r18_sensory_pack' & 'fetish_guidance_pack'

== 2. Dialogue-Anchor Protocol ==
Skill -> Steps: Execute step-01 (Input Validation)
Steps -> State: Init empty forensic-state

Skill -> Steps: Execute step-02 (Pure OCR Extraction)
activate Steps
Steps -> OCRTool: mcp_manga-ocr_ocr_full_page(image_path)
OCRTool --> Steps: Raw Text Block
Steps -> State: Save 'raw_text' independently
deactivate Steps

Skill -> Steps: Execute step-03 (Dialogue Alignment)
activate Steps
Steps -> Steps: Map raw text to character entities
Steps -> State: Save structured dialogue blocks
deactivate Steps

== 3. Visual Forensic Scan ==
Skill -> Steps: Execute step-04 (Environmental Scan)
activate Steps
Steps -> Steps: Pervert Scan Protocol (Fluids, Smells, Clothes)
Steps -> State: Save sensory & visual data
deactivate Steps

== 4. Final Assembly ==
Skill -> Steps: Execute step-05 (Final Report)
Steps -> State: Validate JSON schema compliance
Steps -> Agent: Return forensic-state object
Agent -> User: Display Forensic Artifact
@enduml
